Guy T. HELVERING, Commissioner of Internal Revenue, v. O. J. PHARAOH. No. 1472. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Aug. 28, 1936. Herman Oliphant, Gen. Counsel for the Department of the Treasury, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. C. F. Miller, of Oklahoma City, Okl., for respondent.

Before LEWIS and McDERMOTT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Petition for review dismissed on motion of petitioner.
